DCFS attorneys had also argued that ProPublica Illinois should not be allowed to identify the children.
Martin barred ProPublica Illinois and other news organizations from publishing “the names and/or any other information that would permit the ready identification” of the children or the foster parents involved in a case ProPublica Illinois is investigating.
ProPublica Illinois reporters learned the identities of the children and foster parents independently and outside court hearings.